An	O
advanced	O
telecommunications	O
system	O
is	O
provided	O
for	O
the	O
recognizing	O
of	O
spoken	O
commands	O
over	O
a	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
,	O
satellite	O
telephone	O
,	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
network	O
.	O
In	O
the	O
cellular	O
application	O
,	O
for	O
example	O
,	O
a	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
System	O
interconnects	O
either	O
internally	O
with	O
or	O
as	O
an	O
external	O
peripheral	O
to	O
a	O
cellular	O
telecommunications	O
switch	O
.	O
The	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
System	O
includes	O
an	O
administrative	O
subsystem	O
,	O
a	O
call	O
processing	O
subsystem	O
,	O
a	O
speaker-dependent	O
recognition	O
subsystem	O
,	O
a	O
speaker-independent	O
recognition	O
subsystem	O
,	O
and	O
a	O
data	O
storage	O
subsystem	O
.	O
The	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
System	O
also	O
allows	O
for	O
increased	O
efficiency	O
in	O
the	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
network	O
by	O
integrating	O
with	O
the	O
switch	O
or	O
switches	O
as	O
a	O
shared	O
resource	O
.	O
The	O
administrative	O
subsystem	O
of	O
the	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
System	O
is	O
used	O
to	O
keep	O
statistical	O
logs	O
of	O
pertinent	O
call	O
information	O
.	O
Pre-recorded	O
instructional	O
messages	O
are	O
stored	O
in	O
the	O
memory	O
of	O
the	O
call	O
processing	O
subsystem	O
for	O
instructing	O
a	O
user	O
on	O
his	O
or	O
her	O
progress	O
in	O
using	O
the	O
system	O
.	O
The	O
speaker-independent	O
recognition	O
subsystem	O
allows	O
the	O
user	O
to	O
interact	O
with	O
the	O
system	O
employing	O
non-user	O
specific	O
functions	O
.	O
User	O
specific	O
functions	O
are	O
controlled	O
with	O
the	O
speaker-dependent	O
recognition	O
subsystem	O
.	O
User	O
specific	O
attributes	O
collected	O
by	O
the	O
recognition	O
subsystems	O
are	O
stored	O
in	O
the	O
data	O
storage	O
subsystem	O
.	O

