TECHNICAL	O
FIELD	O
This	O
invention	O
is	O
related	O
to	O
telecommunications	O
systems	O
,	O
and	O
more	O
particularly	O
to	O
an	O
electronic	O
digital	O
signal	O
processor-controlled	O
telecommunications	O
system	O
for	O
the	O
recognition	O
of	O
spoken	O
commands	O
and	O
for	O
the	O
directing	O
of	O
telephone	O
calls	O
based	O
on	O
spoken	O
commands	O
.	O

BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
It	O
is	O
well-known	O
that	O
many	O
of	O
the	O
safety	O
hazards	O
of	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
use	O
could	O
be	O
alleviated	O
by	O
utilizing	O
automatic	O
speech	O
recognition	O
.	O
While	O
telephone-based	O
speech	O
recognition	O
systems	O
are	O
known	O
,	O
cellular	O
voice	O
dialing	O
over	O
a	O
mobile	O
telephone	O
exchange	O
(	O
"	O
MTX	O
"	O
)	O
presents	O
significant	O
challenges	O
for	O
two	O
basic	O
reasons	O
.	O
First	O
,	O
the	O
recognition	O
technology	O
must	O
accommodate	O
a	O
tremendous	O
range	O
of	O
both	O
remotely-mounted	O
and	O
hand-held	O
microphone	O
types	O
.	O
Second	O
,	O
the	O
signal	O
may	O
be	O
band-limited	O
and	O
degraded	O
in	O
transmission	O
to	O
the	O
MTX	O
where	O
the	O
recognition	O
system	O
will	O
be	O
located	O
.	O
Voice-controlled	O
dialers	O
of	O
the	O
prior	O
art	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
taught	O
in	O
U.S.	O
Pat	O
.	O
No.	O
4	O
,	O
853	O
,	O
953	O
to	O
Fujisaki	O
,	O
have	O
not	O
been	O
successfully	O
implemented	O
in	O
the	O
cellular	O
environment	O
.	O

There	O
is	O
therefore	O
a	O
need	O
for	O
voice	O
recognition	O
systems	O
for	O
use	O
in	O
the	O
cellular	O
,	O
sattelite	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
network	O
environments	O
that	O
overcome	O
these	O
and	O
other	O
problems	O
of	O
the	O
prior	O
art	O
and	O
that	O
facilitate	O
the	O
use	O
of	O
voice-dialing	O
and	O
other	O
safety	O
and	O
convenience	O
features	O
.	O

BRIEF	O
SUMMARY	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
It	O
is	O
therefore	O
an	O
object	O
of	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
to	O
describe	O
an	O
implementation	O
of	O
a	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
in	O
a	O
cellular	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
network	O
environment	O
.	O

It	O
is	O
a	O
further	O
object	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
to	O
describe	O
a	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
for	O
use	O
at	O
a	O
mobile	O
telephone	O
exchange	O
(	O
MTX	O
)	O
of	O
a	O
cellular	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
network	O
.	O
The	O
placement	O
of	O
the	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
at	O
the	O
MTX	O
significantly	O
reduces	O
cost	O
and	O
increases	O
reliability	O
by	O
enabling	O
the	O
switch	O
vendor	O
to	O
install	O
and	O
maintain	O
the	O
system	O
in	O
conjunction	O
with	O
the	O
cellular	O
switch	O
.	O

It	O
is	O
another	O
object	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
to	O
describe	O
a	O
cellular	O
voice	O
dialing	O
system	O
for	O
use	O
in	O
or	O
in	O
conjunction	O
with	O
an	O
MTX	O
of	O
a	O
cellular	O
network	O
.	O

It	O
is	O
still	O
another	O
object	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
to	O
use	O
voice	O
recognition	O
techniques	O
to	O
secure	O
access	O
to	O
a	O
cellular	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
network	O
.	O

Another	O
object	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
is	O
to	O
provide	O
for	O
combined	O
use	O
of	O
speaker-dependent	O
and	O
speaker-independent	O
voice	O
recognition	O
and	O
speaker	O
verification	O
techniques	O
in	O
an	O
MTX	O
of	O
a	O
cellular	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
telephone	O
network	O
.	O

These	O
and	O
other	O
objects	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
are	O
provided	O
in	O
an	O
advanced	O
system	O
for	O
the	O
recognizing	O
of	O
spoken	O
commands	O
over	O
the	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
or	O
any	O
personal	O
communications	O
(	O
i	O
.	O
e	O
.	O
,	O
any	O
non-wireline	O
)	O
network	O
.	O
In	O
the	O
cellular	O
application	O
,	O
for	O
example	O
,	O
a	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
System	O
interconnects	O
either	O
internally	O
with	O
or	O
as	O
an	O
external	O
peripheral	O
to	O
a	O
cellular	O
telecommunications	O
MTX	O
switch	O
.	O
The	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
System	O
includes	O
an	O
administrative	O
subsystem	O
