addresses	O
.	O

The	O
invention	O
successfully	O
implements	O
speech	O
recognition	O
in	O
the	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
or	O
personal	O
communications	O
network	O
.	O
Non-wireline	O
networks	O
provide	O
a	O
special	O
challenge	O
to	O
both	O
the	O
recognition	O
algorithm	O
developers	O
as	O
well	O
as	O
the	O
applications	O
developers	O
.	O
The	O
recognition	O
algorithm	O
in	O
conjunction	O
with	O
the	O
system	O
application	O
is	O
insensitive	O
to	O
the	O
radio	O
fading	O
,	O
speech	O
clipping	O
,	O
and	O
speech	O
compression	O
conditions	O
that	O
occur	O
in	O
a	O
non-wireline	O
network	O
.	O
In	O
addition	O
,	O
the	O
recognition	O
algorithm	O
accommodates	O
conditions	O
found	O
in	O
the	O
standard	O
switched	O
network	O
.	O
The	O
invention	O
provides	O
a	O
means	O
of	O
accurately	O
recognizing	O
speech	O
that	O
has	O
limited	O
distortion	O
due	O
to	O
clipping	O
or	O
fading	O
and	O
provides	O
a	O
means	O
of	O
reprompting	O
the	O
user	O
for	O
input	O
when	O
the	O
speech	O
has	O
become	O
too	O
distorted	O
for	O
accurate	O
recognition	O
.	O

Previously	O
,	O
only	O
the	O
best	O
examples	O
of	O
spoken	O
words	O
have	O
been	O
used	O
as	O
tokens	O
for	O
developing	O
speech	O
vocabularies	O
.	O
By	O
collecting	O
speech	O
that	O
has	O
been	O
